	Permissions are symmetric for USER/SUPERVISOR
		Stay with this for the moment.


	Suggestion
	------------
		For the application (ProgramThreads section),
		specify if the application will run in user mode
		or supervisor mode...
		
		Thread specific..

	Suggestion
	----------------
		Interrupt handlers for interrupt levels 1 to 15
		OK.  Thread (0,0) sets up the table..

		Generate a setup_interrupts.s file which calls 
		the C routines 

			ajit_initialize_interrupt_handlers_to_null();
        		ajit_set_interrupt_handler(id1, &(__handler_1));
        		ajit_set_interrupt_handler(id2, &(__handler_2));
        		ajit_set_interrupt_handler(id3, &(__handler_3));
				etc.


	Suggestion
	-----------
		Software trap handlers for software traps ta 1 to ta 15.
		Thread (0,0) sets up the table..

		Generate a setup_trap_handlers.s file which calls 

        		ajit_initialize_sw_trap_handlers_to_null();
        		ajit_set_sw_trap_handler(1, &(__t1_handler));
        		ajit_set_sw_trap_handler(2, &(__t2_handler));
        		ajit_set_sw_trap_handler(3, &(__t3_handler));
        		ajit_set_sw_trap_handler(4, &(__t4_handler));

